Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveVeteran Nollywood actress, Kate Henshaw, on Friday recounted how she almost boarded the ill-fated Dana Air flight that took off from Abuja heading to Lagos on June 3rd, 2012.
Henshaw captioned a photo on Instagram thanking God for saving her.
She said, “ Today marks 10 years since the ill-fated flight took off from Abuja to Lagos. 3rd June, 2012, Flight 0992.”
Revealing how she arrived at the airport late, she said, “I was to be on that flight. I arrived the airport in Abuja late. Anyone who knows me, knows I am never late, for anything. MERCY said no that day. For His goodness and mercy shall follow me, all the days of my life.”
